WARRI – The leadership of Peace, Development, Security and Humanitarian Rights Association of Niger Deltans, in conjunction with Egbema communities has hailed President Muhammadu Buhari-led Federal Government and critical stakeholders who played significant roles which led to the Federal Government’s plan to establish eighteen modular refineries in the Niger Delta region. Comrade Mike Tiemo, the President of the two bodies, in his commendation speech, noted that the Federal Government pronouncement affirming the establishment of the eighteen modular refineries in the Niger Delta is a welcome development that can be described as an expectation that is long overdue. The Niger Delta humanitarian Activist observed that the wonderful gesture of modular refineries coming from the Buhari-led administration is a legacy that will outlive his administration and it will also write the names of all who supported the idea in the good books of history. Olota To Hold First Annual Retreat For Awori Monarchs EKOEXCEL Marks 2022 Int’l Day Of Education According to Tiemo, the establishment of modular refineries in the Niger Delta will tackle and address the problems of perennial pipeline vandalism, the proliferation of illegal refineries, discouragement of crude oil theft, wipe off all sorts of criminal elements, remove unscrupulous acts such as sea piracy, kidnapping, thuggery, scarcity of petroleum products and unemployment. Tiemo stressed that the establishment of modular refineries will also accelerate the multiplayer positive effect of the provision of basic amenities in the communities where the refineries are domiciled. He further explained that the presence of modular refineries will attract more foreign investors to the country and strengthen the laudable and rapid economic recovery plan of the FG. He pointed out that modular refineries in the Niger Delta region will promote capacity building, human capital development, youth/ women empowerment and it will also promote and strengthen the cordal and bilateral relationship which exist between the oil companies and the host communities producing oil and gas. However, Comrade Tiemo remarked that the planned eighteen modular refineries to be executed by the FG which is an average of three per state is a far cry from what is needed to make an appreciatable difference and expected positive impact in solving the problem of acute fuel shortage or scarcity, frequent increase in pump price, shortage of locally refined petroleum products, inability to avert further pollution of the Niger Delta region with illegally sourced crude oil. POLL He appealed to the FG and all relivant stakeholders mentioned above to support this laudable vision of the establishment of Modular Refineries and also to increase the number far more than the eighteen pencilled down earlier by the FG through the Ministry of Environment. Comrade Tiemo called on other relevant Agencies of Government including the Private Sector, particularly the international Oil Companies (IOC,s) to collaborate with the FG to ensure that the idea of establishing Modular Refineries in the Niger Delta region is executed with agility in record timeto adequately address most of the issues of long time neglect and pollution which is already a threat to the life of the people of the Niger Delta region. Comrade Mike Tiemo, who made a special commendation remark in his summation said: “My Special kudos to President Muhammadu Buhari, Vice President, Prof, Yemi Osinbajo, who first made the pronouncement of modular refineries during his visit to the Niger Delta in 2016 in his capacity as Acting President, as a veritable alternative to Artisanal Refineries and today the dream of having Modular Refineries in the Niger Delta is coming to fruition.” He added: “In the same token, my special greeting to the Hon Minister of State for Petroleum, Timipre Sylva, the Hon Minister of State for Environment, Chief Sharon lkeazor, the Hon Minister of Niger Delta Affairs, Senator Godswill Akpabio, the Senior Special Assistant to the President on Niger Delta Affairs, Senator Ita Enang for the good works they are doing concerning the actualization of the establishment of Modular Refineries in the Niger Delta region,” he concluded.